body:
Champions are getting too complex and it&#039;s not a good thing. Now I know as a regular players league may not seem complex, but imagine for new players. It pushes them away from the game and alienates them. Even I, a returning player, had to look up almost every champion I used to know like the back of my hand when I got them in ARAM. And yes, I had to look them up during loading screen because you can&#039;t just quickly read them at the beginning anymore. Before it was like:
&quot;Q makes you run fast and deal more damage next auto&quot;

Now it&#039;s:
&quot;Q makes you run fast, and if you can W the enemy while running fast you will do more damage to him; This will also leave a mark that can be consumed by your E, if you can get this combo off you will be able to cast your R&quot;

Like what happened to all the simplicity? I don&#039;t get why simpleness is a bad thing, honestly. I feel like league is dying as a game you can have fun in after a long day and turning into a job for the LCS big boyz to show off in by doing 5000 pages of homework. If this is all coming from a returning player, imagine how new players feel.

Now let the downvotes and &quot;git gud&quot; comments commence.
